A TRUCK TRAILER OWNED BY HERITAGE TRANSPORT, LLC WAS PARKED AT NUCOR STEEL CORPORATION. APPROXIMATELY, 50 TO 75 POUNDS OF ELECTRIC ARC FURNACE DUST (USEPA HAZARD CODE KO61) SPILLED FROM THE TAILGATE ON THE TRUCK TRAILER. THE SPILL WAS REPORTED AT 0700 ON SEPTEMBER 20, 2001 BY A HERITAGE TRANSPORT, LLC EMPLOYEE. THE INCIDENT WAS REPORTED TO HERITAGE ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICES, LLC PERSONNEL WORKING AT NUCOR STEEL CORPORATION AND NUCOR STEEL CORPORATION REPRESENTATIVES. VERBAL SPILL NOTIFICATIONS WERE PLACED TO THE NATIONAL RESPONSE CENTER(INCIDENT NUMBER 580300) AND THE INDIANA DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMENTAL MANAGEMENT (INCIDENT NUMBER 2001-09-3038) AT 0900 ON SEPTEMBER 20, 2001.  THE SPILL OCCURRED ON A TEMPORARY PARKING STRUCTURE CONSTRUCTED WITH STEEL SLAG MATERIALS. THE AREA OF THE SPILL WAS CONFINED TO AN AREA OF APPROXIMATELY 18 SQUARE FEET. HERITAGE ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICES, LLC PERSONNEL RESPONDED BY REMOVING THE SPILL RESIDUES AND APPROXIMATELY SIX INCHES OF THE STEEL SLAG MATERIALS BENEATH THE SPILL AREA USING A BACKHOE.  THE MATERIAL WAS PLACED IN A DUMP TRAILER AND IS SCHEDULED FOR MANAGEMENT AT HERITAGE ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICES, LLC IN INDIANAPOLIS, INDIANA. CLEAN-UP OF THE SPILL WAS COMPLETED AT APPROXIMATELY 0930 ON SEPTEMBER 20, 2001. A COPY OF THE HAZARDOUS WASTE MANIFEST FOR THE SHIPMENT IS ATTACHED.

column168: AT APPROXIMATELY 5:00 AM ON SEPTEMBER 5, 2001, POLLUTION CONTROL INDUSTRIES'  DRIVER HENRY MADKINS WAS DRIVING SOUTH ON 3RD STREET IN HANNIBAL, MO. AT THE INTERSECTION OF 3RD AND CENTER STREET MR. MADKINS WAS FORCED TO QUICKLY BRAKE HIS TRUCK DUE TO A SUDDEN LIGHT CHANGE AT THE INTERSECTION. WHEN MR. MADKINS BRAKED, THE LIQUID IN HIS TANKER SURGED TO THE NOSE OF THE TANKER AND SLOSHED BACK ALONG THE TOP. THE TANKER MR. MADKINS WAS PULLING HAS TWO 3-INCH PORTS ON THE DOME THAT WERE COVERED AND LOCKED USING A  CAM-LOCK FITTING. THE FORCE OF THE LIQUID HITTING ONE OF THE COVERS CAUSED THE CAM-LOCK TO FAIL, ALLOWING APPROXIMATELY TWO GALLONS OF WASTE MATERIAL TO SPEW OUT. DUE TO THE LOCATION OF THE PORT ON THE TOP CENTER DOME OF THE TANKER, AND HIS ATTENTION TO TRAFFIC CONDITIONS, MR. MADKINS DID NOT SEE THE MATERIAL COME OUT OF THE TANKER, SO, AFTER STOPPING FOR THE LIGHT, HE PROCEEDED TO HIS DESTINATION. HOWEVER, AN OFF DUTY FIREMAN WHO WAS ALSO AT THE INTERSECTION, DID SEE THE MATERIAL COME OUT, AND REPORTED THE SPILL TO THE HANNIBAL FIRE DEPARTMENT.  DAVID HYMERS WITH THE HANNIBAL FIRE DEPARTMENT CONTACTED CONTINENTAL CEMENT AT APPROXIMATELY 11:30 AM AND INFORMED THEM OF THE INCIDENT. SARAH HOFFMAN AND JEFF HEIBEL FROM CONTINENTAL WENT TO THE SCENE. THEY WIPED UP AS MUCH LIQUID AS WAS POSSIBLE AT THAT TIME (MOST OF THE SPILL HAD DRIED), AND REMOVED AS MUCH DRIED DEBRIS AS POSSIBLE. CONTINENTAL NOTIFIED ME OF THE INCIDENT AT ABOUT 12:00 PM, AND ALSO TRIED TO CONTACT JOHN HARK WITH THE MARION COUNTY LEPC. HE WAS CONTACTED AT APPROXIMATELY 3:30 PM, AND ASKED IF ANYONE COULD DECONTAMINATE THE SPILL. CONTINENTAL SENT PERSONNEL WITH ACETONE AND RAGS TO DECON THE AREA. ALL WASTE MATERIAL WAS DISPOSED OF AT CONTINENTAL CEMENT.

AT APPROXIMATELY 07:00 A.M. ON SEPTEMBER 14, 2001 WE HAD A CHEMICAL SPILL OF B142 GEL. SPILL OCCURRED ON COUNTY RD. 2125 IN RUSK COUNTY, TEXAS THIS WAS APPROXIMATELY 0.6 MI EAST OF THE INTERSECTION OF 2125A AND 2125. VOLUME OF SPILL WAS APPROXIMATELY 500 GALLONS. THE SPILL WAS IMMEDIATELY CONTAINED WITH A DIKE. THE DISTRICT WAS NOTIFIED AND WE BEGIN THE PROCESS OF CLEAN UP. THE CONTAMINATED SOIL AREA WAS 120FT. X 30FT. WE CALLED FOR A TRACTOR AND TRUCK TO PICK UP THE SPILL. WE COLLECTED ABOUT 10 YARDS OF CONTAMINATED SOIL AND HAULED BACK TO SCHLUMBERGER FACILITY TO BE TESTED AND DISPOSED OF.  WE NOTIFIED RUSK COUNTY OFFICIALS AND TNRCC. TNRCC TOLD US TO FOLLOW THE FOLLOWING INSTRUCTIONS. 1. CLEAN UP SPILL. 2. TAKE SAMPLES AND HAVE ANALYZED. 3. WRITE A REPORT AND ADDRESS THE FOLLOWING (WHO, WHAT, WHEN, , WHERE AND HOW.) 4. DISPOSE OF THE CONTAMINATED SOIL IN APPROVED LANDFILL. RUSK COUNTY JUDGE SANDRA HODGES ARRIVED AT THE SPILL AREA. SHE SAID WE WERE DOING WHAT NEEDED TO BE DONE. JERRY NORTHCUTT WITH CHEROKEE WATER COMPANY ALSO ARRIVED AT THE SPILL. HE ALSO SAID WE WERE DOING ALL THAT NEEDED TO BE DONE. WE CALLED ANA-LAB TO GO TO THE SPILL AREA AND GET SOIL SAMPLES OF THE SPILL AREA AND BACKGROUND SAMPLES. AFTER TEST RESULTS WE SENT BIG D HAZMAT TEAM TO SITE TO CLEAN MORE OF THE SOIL FROM THE AREA. WE THEN HAD ANA-LAB RETEST. AFTER MORE CLEANING AND TESTING WE GOT AREA TO BACKGROUND RESULTS. TNRCC ACCEPTED THE FINAL TEST RESULTS AS GOOD.
